&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Garda Capital Partners (Garda) is a multi-billion dollar alternative investment firm with over 22 years of experience deploying relative value strategies across fixed income markets for institutional investors. We hire, grow, and mentor great talent and remain steadfast in our commitment to building a culture that helps them succeed. Garda is more than a workplace. We are built on trust, integrity, and a shared vision for how we work together, the enduring relationships we build, and the consistency of our results. Garda&#39;s primary offices are located in Wayzata, New York City, West Palm Beach, Geneva, Zug, Copenhagen, Singapore, and Scottsdale.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Garda is looking to hire &lt;strong&gt;AI Interns&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to be a part of our unique Innovation Lab dedicated to high-impact AI projects. The role will be based out of our Geneva or Zug offices for 6 months and starting as soon as the candidate is available. This is an elite opportunity to join a dedicated innovation unit focused on the research, development, and deployment of cutting-edge AI technologies within the rapidly changing and demanding environment of a global hedge fund.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aid in the development of new lines of business solutions using Language Models (LLMs) and Agentic AI workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support senior staff in designing and implementing complete AI-driven solutions for our front office and risk systems to enhance decision-making velocity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate data extraction, synthesis, and reporting and build bespoke tools for alternative data analysis and signal processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ideas from teams, build out minimum viable products independently, and rapidly iterate via stakeholder feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct feasibility studies on frontier AI and deep learning research to determine its applicability to the firm&#39;s core business challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Desired Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pursuing a Bachelor&#39;s or Master’s Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Physics, or a related quantitative discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A rigorous grasp of computer science fundamentals, including data structures, algorithms, and asynchronous programming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with the Python ecosystem (specifically libraries like pandas, NumPy, and PyTorch/TensorFlow).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated interest in financial markets and trading.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial spirit, strong problem solving skills, superb organizational skills, sound judgment, and a client-focused approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embraces a shared drive to learn, improve, and achieve lasting impact as part of a high-energy team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates curiosity and a desire to continuously learn, innovate, and improve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work cross-functionally, build strong working relationships, and adapt as priorities or market conditions evolve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gardacp.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/Candidate_Privacy_Notice.pdf&quot;&gt;Candidate Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Garda Capital Partners (Garda) is a multi-billion dollar alternative investment firm with over 22 years of experience deploying relative value strategies across fixed income markets for institutional investors. We hire, grow, and mentor great talent and remain steadfast in our commitment to building a culture that helps them succeed. Garda is more than a workplace. We are built on trust, integrity, and a shared vision for how we work together, the enduring relationships we build, and the consistency of our results. Garda&#39;s primary offices are located in Wayzata, New York City, West Palm Beach, Geneva, Zug, Copenhagen, Singapore, and Scottsdale.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Garda is seeking a Cyber Security Analyst with experience to support day-to-day security operations, including vulnerability management, IAM, incident response, access reviews, and security awareness initiatives. The role also involves partnering with stakeholders across the firm on security policies, vendor due diligence, and other security projects, with financial services experience preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run vulnerability management and patching: track findings to closure, prioritize remediation, and report on progress&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct periodic user and privileged access reviews and help maintain least-privilege access across systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support identity and access management (IAM) operations, including provisioning, deprovisioning, and access policy enforcement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle day-to-day security operations, monitoring, and routine investigations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage security awareness training and phishing simulation programs and follow up on results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Triage and respond to incident escalations from our managed detection and response provider, driving them to resolution and escalating where appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take ownership of analyst-level security tasks and recurring operational work to support the broader team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build effective working relationships with stakeholders across Garda&#39;s offices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Policies / procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vendor due diligence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on security related initiatives as directed by the security architect&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Desired Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years in an infrastructure or security role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in financial services is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage and prioritize multiple tasks and deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source control and pipeline security operations (GitSecOps) experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of core security concepts: network protocols, firewalls, common attack vectors, and risk&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional certifications such as CompTIA Security+, CISM, or CISSP are a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented, with strong verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

